<br>
They walk miles til finally they come to a farmhouse. they knock on the door and ask the farmer if they can spend the night.<br>
<br>
Being a nice fellow, the farmer tells them sure, but I only have two spare beds, one of you has to sleep in the barn. the Buddhist speaks up, saying as he has lived a life of peverty and depreavation it will not be hard for him to spell in a barn.<br>
<br>
Off to bed they go. Shortly after there is a knock on the door, and the Buddhist is standing there looking rather ashamed and upset. Sorry he says, but there are cows in the barn, and I know they are destined to be eaten, and I cannot abide by that, my faith prevents it. the Jew says, worry not friend, I can take your place, my peoples were homeless for centuries.<br>
<br>
Off they all go to bed again. Again, not long after there is a knock on the door. The Jew is standing there looking a bit put out. I am sorry, he says, but my faith does not allow me to lie with swine, and there are many pigs in your barn.<br>
<br>
They all turn to look at the lawyer. Fine, he says, I will sleep in the barn, it will remind me of the fine pro-bono work I did when I first got out of law school.<br>
<br>
Once again, off to bed they go. A few minutes later there is a knock on the door. The oldest bull and sow are standing there. In unison they say, No Fucking Way are we sleeping in the barn as long as the scumbag is there.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Fundin Stoutheart<br>
