To quote you again: &quot;Words are words. Intentions matter.&quot;  Wrong again, dumbass.  What you intended has absolutely nothing to do with it.  It's offensive if a reasonable person, upon hearing it, would be offended.  Regardless of whether you whine on about &quot;but I didn't mean it to be offensive, really I didn't!&quot;  Do you know how many people have gotten their asses canned in this country for bantering with African-Americans and calling them &quot;niggah&quot;?  Even if those same African-Americans used that same word earlier in the conversation to refer to themselves?<br>
